## Two-layer system

This project uses Tailwind CSS v4 and MUI v9 together:

- **Tailwind** — layout, spacing, typography, colour, responsive breakpoints.
- **MUI** — interactive components with built-in accessibility: `Button`, `TextField`, `Select`, `Dialog`, `Snackbar`, `CircularProgress`, etc.

Use the right tool for the job. Do not rebuild MUI primitives from scratch with Tailwind, and do not fight MUI's structure with deep Tailwind overrides.

## Tailwind

- Apply Tailwind classes directly on JSX elements for layout and spacing.
- Use Tailwind for `flex`, `grid`, `gap`, `p-*`, `m-*`, `text-*`, `font-*`, `rounded-*`, `border`, `shadow`.
- Use responsive prefixes (`sm:`, `md:`, `lg:`) for breakpoints — do not write media queries manually.
- Use Tailwind's `dark:` variant for dark mode where applicable.
- Do not use arbitrary values (`w-[347px]`) unless a design token genuinely doesn't exist.

```tsx
// Correct — Tailwind for layout
<div className="flex flex-col gap-4 p-6 max-w-2xl mx-auto">
  <RecipeCard recipe={recipe} />
</div>

// Wrong — inline styles for layout
<div style={{ display: 'flex', flexDirection: 'column', gap: '16px' }}>
```

## MUI components

- Import MUI components from `@mui/material`.
- Use the `size` and `variant` props instead of overriding dimensions manually.
- For minor visual tweaks on MUI components, prefer the `sx` prop over adding a Tailwind class on the MUI component root.
- Do not wrap a MUI `Button` in a `<div>` just to add spacing — use Tailwind on the surrounding container.

```tsx
// Correct
<Button variant="contained" size="small" onClick={onSave}>
  Save recipe
</Button>

// Wrong — reimplementing what MUI already provides
<button className="bg-blue-600 text-white px-4 py-2 rounded">Save recipe</button>
```

## MUI + Tailwind conflict avoidance

- MUI renders with Emotion; Tailwind injects via the Vite plugin. Specificity conflicts are rare but can occur.
- If a Tailwind class on a MUI component root has no effect, use `sx` instead.
- Do not apply MUI `sx` for layout concerns that Tailwind handles — keep concerns separated.

```tsx
// Correct — Tailwind on the wrapper, sx for MUI-specific tweak
<div className="mt-4">
  <TextField
    sx={{ '& .MuiOutlinedInput-root': { borderRadius: 2 } }}
    label="Recipe title"
    {...register('title')}
  />
</div>

// Wrong — fighting two systems in one place
<TextField className="mt-4 w-full" sx={{ marginTop: '16px' }} />
```

## Colour and typography

- Use Tailwind colour utilities (`text-slate-700`, `bg-amber-50`, etc.) on non-MUI elements.
- For MUI components, use the MUI theme or `sx` with theme tokens (`color: 'text.secondary'`).
- Do not hardcode hex values — use Tailwind's palette or MUI's theme.

## Do not

- Do not use the `style` prop for anything Tailwind or MUI can handle.
- Do not import `@emotion/react` or `@emotion/styled` directly — MUI manages Emotion internally.
- Do not create custom CSS files for component-level styles; use Tailwind utilities instead.
- Do not use `!important` overrides.
